40|$|The thesis {{describes}} "Letter of Credit" {{as one of}} {{the oldest}} and safest instruments used in international trade. Chapter one deals with the basic characteristics <b>of</b> <b>Letter</b> <b>of</b> <b>Credit,</b> the whilst second chapter describes advantages and disadvantages of this financial instrument. The next part is devoted to the course <b>of</b> <b>Letter</b> <b>of</b> <b>Credit,</b> analyzing the process from negotiating the terms <b>of</b> the <b>credit</b> and its opening to its draw down. In chapter four, the current and future development <b>of</b> <b>Letter</b> <b>of</b> <b>Credit</b> is characterized, including the development of its electronic form. The last chapter is a case study, where the main documents related to <b>Letter</b> <b>of</b> <b>Credit</b> are analyzed, including pointing out errors, which are most often made by bank customers and finally the comparison of fees associated with <b>Letter</b> <b>of</b> <b>Credit</b> in selected banks is performed...|$|R
